{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/hkirat/awesome-chess/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"93b7632d-25dd-5f81-a21f-cf7cce7f5252","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-chess-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-chess-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome chess awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Chess <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<p>A curated list of assets availible on the Internet related to chess.</p>\n<p><em>Inspired by the <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\">awesome</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">164.8k</span></span></a> list thing. You might want to read the complete <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\">awesome</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">164.8k</span></span></a> list.</em></p>\n<h3 id=\"contributing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contributing\" aria-label=\"contributing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contributing</h3>\n<p>Kindly go through <a href=\"https://github.com/hkirat/awesome-chess/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#contribution-guidelines\">Contribution Guidelines</a> first.</p>\n<h2 id=\"content\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#content\" aria-label=\"content permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Content</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#books\">Books</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fen-parsers\">FEN Parsers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#move-validators\">Move Validators</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bots\">Bots</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#websites\">Websites</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#boards\">Boards</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#board-notations\">Board Notations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pieces\">Pieces</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#talks\">Talks</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h2>\n<p><em>Books to read on chess.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://kairavacademydotcom.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/john-thursby-75-chess-problems.pdf\">Chess Problems</a> - Collection of chess puzzles.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/5614/pg5614-images.html\">Chess strategy</a> - HTML version of chess strategy by Edward Lasker.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.chesscity.com/PDF/Sicilian_Dragon_Black_Attacks_ssd.pdf\">Sicilian Dragon</a> - Attacking plans for black.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"fen-parsers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#fen-parsers\" aria-label=\"fen parsers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>FEN Parsers</h2>\n<p><em>Forsyth–Edwards Notation (FEN) is a standard notation for describing a particular board position of a chess game.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/tlehman/fenparser\">fenparser by tlehman</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/tlehman/fenparser\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8</span></span></a> - A parser for Forsyth-Edwards Notation wriitten in Python.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ucarion/fen\">fen by ucarion</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ucarion/fen\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a> - A Rust Forsyth-Edwards notation parser with proper error handling.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/andyherbert/fen-diagram\">fen-diagram by andyherbert</a> - JavaScript for generating chess diagrams using Forsyth-Edwards notation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"bots\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#bots\" aria-label=\"bots permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Bots</h2>\n<p><em>Bots are algorithms involving artificial intelligence to play against a user.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/benwr/latrunculorum\">latrunculorum</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/benwr/latrunculorum\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a> - A simple chess bot in Python.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jfabeel/Chessbot\">Chessbot</a> - Bot written in Java.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"move-validators\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#move-validators\" aria-label=\"move validators permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Move Validators</h2>\n<p><em>Validators are tools for checking authenticity of a move.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jhlywa/chess.js\">chess.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jhlywa/chess.js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.3k</span></span></a> - chess.js, Structured code for chess authentication.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/chess\">npm chess package</a> - An algebraic notation driven chess engine that can validate board position and produce a list of viable moves.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cgearhart/Chessnut.git\">Chessnut</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cgearhart/Chessnut.git\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">36</span></span></a> - Chessnut is a simple chess board model written in Python. It provides functionality of parsing FEN and generating a list of legal moves for each FEN representation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"websites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#websites\" aria-label=\"websites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Websites</h2>\n<p><em>Websites include platforms for people to play chess.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://multiplayerchess.com\">multiplayerchess.com</a> - A simple single page chess playing application facilitating the play of chess.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://en.lichess.org/\">lichess.org</a> - One of the most mature platforms for playing chess on the internet. It is open source too. It is equipped with daily puzzles and an TV to spectate other matches.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chess24.com/en/play/chess\">chess24.com</a> - Play as well as learn chess from chess24 with the best of tutorials.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://play.chessbase.com/js/apps/playchess/\">chessbase.com</a> - Lucrative, single page application for playing chess.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.chess.com/\">chess.com</a> - Learn and play chess with over 5 million other users.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.chesscademy.com/\">chesscademy.com</a> - Watch videos, solve puzzles, and play games. All for free. (Works similar to Khan Academy.)</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://chesstempo.com\">chesstempo.com</a> - Online chess tactics training site.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://chessprogramming.wikispaces.com/\">chessprogramming.wikispaces.com</a> - Repository of information about programming computers to play chess.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://freechess.org/\">freechess.org</a> - The 'Free Internet Chess Server' (FICS) is one of the oldest Internet chess servers. There are lots of client applications for almost every device, operation system or webbrowser available.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"boards\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#boards\" aria-label=\"boards permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Boards</h2>\n<p><em>Boards are tools for encapsulating the process of rendering a board.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/oakmac/chessboardjs/\">Chessboard.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/oakmac/chessboardjs/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.5k</span></span></a> - chessboard.js is a standalone JavaScript chess board.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/laat/chess-board\">chess-board</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/laat/chess-board\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">19</span></span></a> - A web component for displaying chess positions. It takes FEN string as input and renders the board as output.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bmarini/jchess\">jchess</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bmarini/jchess\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">85</span></span></a> - A jQuery based JavaScript library for parsing and displaying chess games. Currently takes FEN and PGN as inputs.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/caustique/chessboard-js\">Chessboard-js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/caustique/chessboard-js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">24</span></span></a> - A responsive mobile-first JavaScript chessboard library.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"board-notations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#board-notations\" aria-label=\"board notations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Board Notations</h2>\n<p><em>Notations are a way of expressing the properties of the board in textual format. <a href=\"http://chess.eusa.ed.ac.uk/Chess/Rules/notation.html\">Tutorial on Chess Notations</a>.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forsyth%E2%80%93Edwards_Notation\">FEN</a> - A FEN \"record\" defines a particular game position, all in one text line and using only the ASCII character set.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www6.chessclub.com/help/PGN-spec\">PNG</a> - PGN is structured \"for easy reading and writing by human users and for easy parsing and generation by computer programs.\"</li>\n<li>Other Notations\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_notation_(chess)\">Algebraic Chess Notation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICCF_numeric_notation\">ICCF numeric notation</a> - Official chess game notation for all International Correspondence Chess Federation games.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www6.chessclub.com/chessviewer/smith.html\">Smith Chess Notation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descriptive_notation\">Descriptive Notation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"pieces\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pieces\" aria-label=\"pieces permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pieces</h2>\n<p><em>This includes the tools for getting artwork for various pieces of chess.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:470700\">Spiral Pieces in 3-D</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:PNG_chess_pieces/Standard_transparent\">Pieces on Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_symbols_in_Unicode\">Chess Pieces in Unicode</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.flaticon.com/search/chess\">Icons on flaticons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://thenounproject.com/search/?q=chess\">Icons on thenounproject</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"talks\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#talks\" aria-label=\"talks permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Talks</h2>\n<p><em>Talks on chess.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fPopQaY7Og4\">Understanding Chess Mastery</a> -Talk on understanding chess mastery by Jennifer Shahade.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A3yDvM8aplY\">How Chess Can Revolutionize Learning</a> - Talk on how chess can revolutionize learning by Cody Pomeranz.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v34NqCbAA1c\">Working backward to solve problems</a> - Talk on working backward to solve problems by Maurice Ashley</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lgCSo1Txw3c\">Chess Life</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7EuxVOgrEig\">Why Chess is Boring </a> - Talk on why chess is boring by Bobby Fischer</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p027ysBt0_M\">Chess Peeps</a></li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#awesome-chess-awesome\">Awesome Chess <img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#contributing\">Contributing</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#content\">Content</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#books\">Books</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#fen-parsers\">FEN Parsers</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#bots\">Bots</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#move-validators\">Move Validators</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#websites\">Websites</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#boards\">Boards</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#board-notations\">Board Notations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#pieces\">Pieces</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#talks\">Talks</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"awesome-chess-awesome","value":"Awesome Chess Awesome","depth":1},{"id":"contributing","value":"Contributing","depth":3},{"id":"content","value":"Content","depth":2},{"id":"books","value":"Books","depth":2},{"id":"fen-parsers","value":"FEN Parsers","depth":2},{"id":"bots","value":"Bots","depth":2},{"id":"move-validators","value":"Move Validators","depth":2},{"id":"websites","value":"Websites","depth":2},{"id":"boards","value":"Boards","depth":2},{"id":"board-notations","value":"Board Notations","depth":2},{"id":"pieces","value":"Pieces","depth":2},{"id":"talks","value":"Talks","depth":2}]},"awesomeList":{"repo":"hkirat/awesome-chess","description":"Chess!","descriptionHTML":"<div>Chess!</div>"},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-27T23:24:21.943Z"},"previous":{"id":"c174aec9-1429-54f2-a18d-057d70e3a